§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ An ❬affine transformation❭ is one which maps an affine
    combination of two vectors to the affine combination of their
    results under the same transformation. ⦉

  ‖ These are sometimes called ❬affine functions❭. ⦉
